<subSubSection id="C3116516DA0FFFA475A0FE14FE0C0370" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="369" pageId="5" pageNumber="368" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB4369DDA0FFFA775A0FE14FE57065D" blockId="5.[151,1436,417,586]" pageId="5" pageNumber="368">
<emphasis id="B97FEA8FDA0FFFA775A0FE14FEE40615" bold="true" box="[199,372,489,514]" pageId="5" pageNumber="368">Redescription.</emphasis>
Length of forewing 14.0–18.0mm; forewing expanse 26.0–36.7mm. Head, thorax and abdomen resembling those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D1EDA0FFFA77491FDF3FDC10632" authority="Osada &amp; Sakai &amp; Hirowatari, 2016" authorityName="Osada &amp; Sakai &amp; Hirowatari" authorityYear="2016" box="[502,593,525,549]" class="Insecta" family="Tineidae" genus="Scardia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="368" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fusca" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B97FEA8FDA0FFFA77491FDF3FDC10632" box="[502,593,525,549]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="368">S. fusca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B97FEA8FDA0FFFA7773BFDF0FD290631" bold="true" box="[604,697,525,550]" pageId="5" pageNumber="368">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24C57F4DA0FFFA7773BFDF0FD290631" box="[604,697,525,550]" pageId="5" pageNumber="368" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, but different as follows: Vertex and face roughly clothed with yellowish white long hairs.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF746615DA0FFFA775F0F869FEC303F0" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1053651/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="368" targetBox="[169,1404,624,1911]" targetPageId="5">
<paragraph id="8BB4369DDA0FFFA775F0F869FEC303F0" blockId="5.[151,1436,1940,2023]" pageId="5" pageNumber="368">
<emphasis id="B97FEA8FDA0FFFA775F0F869FE8003BE" bold="true" box="[151,272,1940,1962]" pageId="5" pageNumber="368">FIGURE 5</emphasis>
. Male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D1EDA0FFFA774B8F869FDF303BD" authorityName="Zagulajev" authorityYear="1965" box="[479,611,1940,1962]" class="Insecta" family="Tineidae" genus="Scardia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="368" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amurensis">
<emphasis id="B97FEA8FDA0FFFA774B8F869FDF303BD" box="[479,611,1940,1962]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="368">
S. 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D1EDA0FFFA7749BF868FDF303BD" box="[508,611,1941,1962]" pageId="5" pageNumber="368" rank="species" species="amurensis">amurensis</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. A: whole genitalia except aedeagus, lateral view. B: Uncus, dorsal view. C: Genitalia except valva, ventral view. D: Valva, inner view. E: Anellus and juxta, lateral view. F: Aedeagus, lateral view. G: 
<emphasis id="B97FEA8FDA0FFFA775F0F82FFF5B03F0" box="[151,203,2002,2023]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="368">Ditto</emphasis>
, dorsal view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption id="DF746615DA0CFFA475F0FA78FE8A01AD" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1053653/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="369" targetBox="[170,1426,211,1370]" targetPageId="6">
