<paragraph id="8BB4369DDA0CFFA475A0FA1BFEDC0250" blockId="6.[151,1436,1510,2003]" pageId="6" pageNumber="369">
Wing markings (
<figureCitation id="13302A18DA0CFFA474ECFA1BFE7701E8" box="[395,487,1510,1535]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1287,1309]" captionTargetBox="[411,1179,205,1247]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[396,1192,195,1263]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Adults of Scardia species from Japan. A: S. fusca sp. nov., holotype ♂. B: S. amurensis ♂." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1053643/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="369">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
): Forewing and hindwing resembling those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D1EDA0CFFA47174FA1AFBFE01E8" authority="Osada &amp; Sakai &amp; Hirowatari, 2016" authorityName="Osada &amp; Sakai &amp; Hirowatari" authorityYear="2016" box="[1043,1134,1511,1535]" class="Insecta" family="Tineidae" genus="Scardia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="369" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fusca" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B97FEA8FDA0CFFA47174FA1AFBFE01E8" box="[1043,1134,1511,1535]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="369">S. fusca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24C57F4DA0CFFA4711DFA1BFB4701E8" box="[1146,1239,1510,1535]" pageId="6" pageNumber="369" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B97FEA8FDA0CFFA4711DFA1BFB4701E8" bold="true" box="[1146,1239,1510,1535]" pageId="6" pageNumber="369">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, but different as follows: Forewing upperside bordered with yellowish white along dorsum and termen. Hindwing upperside pale brownish white.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB4369DDA0CFFA475A0F9AFFB8E027C" blockId="6.[151,1436,1510,2003]" box="[199,1054,1618,1643]" pageId="6" pageNumber="369">
