<figureCitation id="13302A18DA0CFFA4741CF9AFFE44027C" box="[379,468,1618,1643]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1400,1422]" captionTargetBox="[444,1143,205,1368]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[426,1154,193,1385]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. wing venations of Scardia species. A: S. fusca sp. nov., ♂. B: S. amurensis ♂." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1053645/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="369">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
): Wing venation resembling that of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D1EDA0CFFA47601F9AEFC2D027C" authority="Osada &amp; Sakai &amp; Hirowatari, 2016" authorityName="Osada &amp; Sakai &amp; Hirowatari" authorityYear="2016" box="[870,957,1619,1643]" class="Insecta" family="Tineidae" genus="Scardia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="369" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fusca" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B97FEA8FDA0CFFA47601F9AEFC2D027C" box="[870,957,1619,1643]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="369">S. fusca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24C57F4DA0CFFA476A3F9AFFB8E027C" box="[964,1054,1618,1643]" pageId="6" pageNumber="369" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B97FEA8FDA0CFFA476A3F9AFFB8E027C" bold="true" box="[964,1054,1618,1643]" pageId="6" pageNumber="369">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB4369DDA0CFFA475A0F98BFEF802EC" blockId="6.[151,1436,1510,2003]" pageId="6" pageNumber="369">
Male genitalia (
<figureCitation id="13302A18DA0CFFA47410F98BFE2C0298" box="[375,444,1654,1679]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1940,1962]" captionTargetBox="[169,1404,624,1911]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[159,1419,610,1924]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 5. Male genitalia of S. amurensis. A: whole genitalia except aedeagus, lateral view. B: Uncus, dorsal view. C: Genitalia except valva, ventral view. D: Valva, inner view. E: Anellus and juxta, lateral view. F: Aedeagus, lateral view. G: Ditto, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1053651/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="369">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
): Male genitalia resembling those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D1EDA0CFFA47638F98AFC260298" authority="Osada &amp; Sakai &amp; Hirowatari, 2016" authorityName="Osada &amp; Sakai &amp; Hirowatari" authorityYear="2016" box="[863,950,1655,1679]" class="Insecta" family="Tineidae" genus="Scardia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="369" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fusca" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B97FEA8FDA0CFFA47638F98AFC260298" box="[863,950,1655,1679]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="369">S. fusca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24C57F4DA0CFFA476DAF98BFB870298" box="[957,1047,1654,1679]" pageId="6" pageNumber="369" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B97FEA8FDA0CFFA476DAF98BFB870298" bold="true" box="[957,1047,1654,1679]" pageId="6" pageNumber="369">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, but different as follows: Width of base of uncus similar to length of uncus. Gnathos and subscaphium absent. Vinculum broad; saccus broad with rounded apex. Valva 1/2 as wide as height of ring, valval apodeme 1/4 times as long as length of valva. Carina of phallus projecting.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB4369DDA0CFFA475A0F8FBFE0C0370" blockId="6.[151,1436,1510,2003]" pageId="6" pageNumber="369">
Female genitalia (
<figureCitation id="13302A18DA0CFFA474F0F8FBFE710308" box="[407,481,1798,1823]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1413,1435]" captionTargetBox="[170,1426,211,1370]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,193,1392]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 6. Female genitalia of S. amurensis. A: whole genitalia, lateral view. B: Terminalia, ventral view. C: Genital plate, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1053653/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="369">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
): Female genitalia resembling those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D1EDA0CFFA476D6F8FAFB9C0308" authority="Osada &amp; Sakai &amp; Hirowatari, 2016" authorityName="Osada &amp; Sakai &amp; Hirowatari" authorityYear="2016" box="[945,1036,1799,1823]" class="Insecta" family="Tineidae" genus="Scardia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="369" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fusca" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B97FEA8FDA0CFFA476D6F8FAFB9C0308" box="[945,1036,1799,1823]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="369">S. fusca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24C57F4DA0CFFA47171F8FBFBE40308" box="[1046,1140,1798,1823]" pageId="6" pageNumber="369" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B97FEA8FDA0CFFA47171F8FBFBE40308" bold="true" box="[1046,1140,1798,1823]" pageId="6" pageNumber="369">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, but different as follows. Genital plate with a pair of rounded quadrate lamellae; apical 1/4 of digitiform process extending beyond posterior margin of genital plate.
</paragraph>
