<subSubSection id="C3116516DA0DFFA575A0F920FEDC0376" pageId="7" pageNumber="370" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB4369DDA0DFFA575A0F920FEDC0376" blockId="7.[151,1436,1396,1889]" pageId="7" pageNumber="370">
<emphasis id="B97FEA8FDA0DFFA575A0F920FEAB02E1" bold="true" box="[199,315,1757,1782]" pageId="7" pageNumber="370">Remarks.</emphasis>
The male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D1EDA0DFFA57752F920FC9402E2" authorityName="Zagulajev" authorityYear="1965" box="[565,772,1757,1781]" class="Insecta" family="Tineidae" genus="Scardia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amurensis">
<emphasis id="B97FEA8FDA0DFFA57752F920FC9402E2" box="[565,772,1757,1781]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="370">Scardia amurensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D1EDA0DFFA5765EF920FC0002E2" authority="Osada &amp; Sakai &amp; Hirowatari, 2016" authorityName="Osada &amp; Sakai &amp; Hirowatari" authorityYear="2016" box="[825,912,1757,1781]" class="Insecta" family="Tineidae" genus="Scardia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fusca" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B97FEA8FDA0DFFA5765EF920FC0002E2" box="[825,912,1757,1781]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="370">S. fusca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24C57F4DA0DFFA576F0F920FC6002E1" box="[919,1008,1757,1782]" pageId="7" pageNumber="370" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B97FEA8FDA0DFFA576F0F920FC6002E1" bold="true" box="[919,1008,1757,1782]" pageId="7" pageNumber="370">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
are similar to those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D1EDA0DFFA57188F920FAFD02E2" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1794" box="[1263,1389,1757,1781]" class="Insecta" family="Tineidae" genus="Scardia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boletella">
<emphasis id="B97FEA8FDA0DFFA57188F920FAFD02E2" box="[1263,1389,1757,1781]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="370">S. boletella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D1EDA0DFFA575F0F8FCFE89030F" box="[151,281,1793,1816]" class="Insecta" family="Tineidae" genus="Scardia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caucasia">
<emphasis id="B97FEA8FDA0DFFA575F0F8FCFE89030F" box="[151,281,1793,1816]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="370">S. caucasia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, in lateral view, but the uncal lobes are slenderer, and not stout as in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D1EDA0DFFA5715EF8FCFB29030E" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1794" box="[1081,1209,1793,1817]" class="Insecta" family="Tineidae" genus="Scardia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boletella">
<emphasis id="B97FEA8FDA0DFFA5715EF8FCFB29030E" box="[1081,1209,1793,1817]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="370">S. boletella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D1EDA0DFFA57194F8FCFAE5030F" box="[1267,1397,1793,1816]" class="Insecta" family="Tineidae" genus="Scardia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caucasia">
<emphasis id="B97FEA8FDA0DFFA57194F8FCFAE5030F" box="[1267,1397,1793,1816]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="370">S. caucasia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In addition, in the two Japanese species, the digitiform processes of the female are slenderer than those of other 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D1EDA0DFFA575F0F8B4FF7D0376" authorityName="Treitschke" authorityYear="1830" box="[151,237,1865,1889]" class="Insecta" family="Tineidae" genus="Scardia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97FEA8FDA0DFFA575F0F8B4FF7D0376" box="[151,237,1865,1889]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="370">Scardia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
